    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Austria)/7–2045:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 776<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20">July 20,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 143. Action <gloss target="#t_AmEmbassy1">AmEmbassy</gloss> London,
                    information Department of State Washington, D. C. <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1"
                        >AFHQ</gloss> Caserta, Italy please pass <gloss target="#t_USPolAd1"
                        >USPolAd</gloss> Florence, Italy.</p>
                <p>The President has approved the draft agreements on control machinery in Austria
                    and Zones of Occupation in Austria as recommended by the <gloss target="#t_EAC1"
                        >EAC</gloss>. You are authorized to sign<note n="1" xml:id="d776fn1">The
                        agreements had already been signed <hi rend="italic">ad referendum</hi>.
                        Their approval was discussed at the Fourth Plenary Meeting, July 20. See <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_176">p. 176</ref>.
                        Notification of approval by the United States Government was given on July
                        24.</note> these agreements on behalf of the US Government and to notify the
                        <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss> of their approval by the US
                    Government.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
